HEADWORD: Pretervection
<hw>Pre`ter*vec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praetervectio</ets>, fr. <ets>praetervehere</ets> to carry beyond.
See <er>Invection</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of carrying past or
beyond.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Abp. Potter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
